TWO STARS FOR THE WORST CUSTOMER SERVICE EXPERIENCE OF ANY APP, EVER. is a bummer. This is one of the better interval timers for Android, though I find the settings U.I. unappealing, and not all that intuitive, especially in comparison to the Apple version. As long as you do not need any help from this developer, or expect the usual customer service courtesies, you'll be fine. When I inquired about my inability to import timers from the web, I described exactly what I was doing (taping the download...). The developer responded without any sort of polite greeting that you might expect, as in "Sorry you're having trouble with Seconds Pro, let's see if we can figure this out," etc, but instead explained how to import and the asked me "what are you doing differently?" Um, nothing.  His response was essentially, "it's just Android then, sorry, I can't help you." That was it. No "try this," or "try that," just "to bad so sad." I asked if I'd get better service if I had an Apple Device, and he said, "Probably, because I make 10x the revenue there!"  This developer clearly does not like developing for Android.

This app rocks! Very nice UI makes it easy to create a range of different custom timers. You can name each interval (and give it a specific color theme too) so you just look at the screen and know your next drill! Save and share too :-) Just be sure to spend some time to set up your timers well: choose the best type of timer and add names with descriptions of the intervals.   Here is a sample from the list of intervals I set up for a 10-level fingerboard training (you see the list like that on the timer's screen and the active level is highlighted). They run automatically one after the other and you have the option to add a 10 sec preparation interval in between them to get ready for the next step: Level 1: 15" hang + 1 pullup - outer jugs, 45" rest (counts 15", 4", 45") Level 2: 12" offset hang (each hand), outer jug + deep three finger pockets, 45" rest (counts 12", 5", 12", 45") I could never remember the 10 levels and with notes in hand and a timer I never made it to the next grip on time so I rested too long. Now I just hit start and go through the entire routine, and I can simply skip a level if I want to, repeat a level, pause, and more... Best buy!!! Enjoy...
